  <md:title>Levels of Measurement for Geneseo Data Course</md:title>
  <md:abstract>This module discusses the different scales used and levels of measurement used to quantify variables. The main terms discussed are Nominal, Ordinal, Interval, and Ratio scales. This module is largely the work of David Lane, with (hopefully) minor presentation changes to make it fit smoothly in SUNY Geneseo's prototype non-specialists' introduction to data.</md:abstract>
